navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"1899ebd9e323dd6f12ebe2f68a8004f2888137808b7ceb8c58ccd0d5c27489d4","event_uuid":"31e1ec76-0b0b-48f3-9a3f-257c09853d80","position":{"commit_sha":"5bbfe623767686d16761f64b6dbd47e9f7d1bfc2","position":"1784441507941264001-31e1ec76-0b0b-48f3-9a3f-257c09853d80"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"0ebb71f52e838d1106d4f8e2980461c4103599b0c368043a887f0973ba230717","event_uuid":"76b27a3d-271c-4c72-b6b0-22742bbea8b9","position":{"commit_sha":"a0d7e4c1cf25f09cf40ec999f5d598d03152ab02","position":"1784441650857923283-76b27a3d-271c-4c72-b6b0-22742bbea8b9"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"6e3fbad8-702f-4987-ad70-cc88122eea43","comments":[],"created_at":1784416760378112001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"b8865250-f43d-40e4-ab96-c0c67bd992d0","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"c085-6d11-d68d-422a"}],"description":"## What\nThe going-forward compact metrics snapshot: a small JSON record appended per CI run (and readable by the command) persisting point-in-time code-health numbers whose history is otherwise ephemeral — coverage %, complexity distribution, clone count — so their movement accrues.\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/metrics/snapshot.py` — new: `write_snapshot(dict)` appends a timestamped record to a committed NDJSON file; `read_snapshots(since,until)` yields in-range records for the registry.\n- `.gitignore` — add `!.rebar/metrics-snapshots.ndjson` to surgically un-ignore the store. The repo gitignores ALL `.rebar/` contents via a blanket `.rebar/*` rule (line 20) and tracks specific files with per-file `!`-negations (e.g. `!.rebar/criteria_routing.json`); WITHOUT this negation line the snapshot file is silently gitignored and the series never persists.\n- `.rebar/metrics-snapshots.ndjson` — new committed artifact (one snapshot per line). **It lives under the tracked `.rebar/` store, NOT under `reports/`**: `/reports/` is gitignored (`.gitignore:74`), so a snapshot file there would never be committed and the trend series would silently never accumulate. `.rebar/` is already tracked in git (e.g. `.rebar/criteria_routing.json`), so snapshots persist and sync.\n- `tests/unit/metrics/test_snapshot.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nCoverage/complexity/clone are computed at a point in time; their trend needs a stored series, which does not exist today. An append-only NDJSON snapshot (not a new event type) is the lowest-friction durable store; it lives under the tracked `.rebar/` store so it is committed and synced (unlike the gitignored `reports/`, which holds only ephemeral CI artifacts). The command reads it for trend metrics, and until a snapshot exists a metric reports `unavailable`. Append-only and additive.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit: `write_snapshot` then `read_snapshots` round-trips; a range filter excludes out-of-range records; a malformed line is skipped without raising.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/metrics/test_snapshot.py` passes: a written snapshot is read back within its date range (`assert rec in read_snapshots(since,until)`) and excluded outside it.\n- [ ] a corrupt/truncated NDJSON line is skipped and the reader still returns the valid records — unit test asserts count equals the valid-record count.\n- [ ] the snapshot store path is `.rebar/metrics-snapshots.ndjson` (a git-tracked path), verified by the test writing under `.rebar/` and asserting the file is not matched by the repo's `.gitignore` — so the going-forward series actually persists.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/snapshot.py","reason":"snapshot writer/reader"},{"path":".rebar/metrics-snapshots.ndjson","reason":"snapshot store (tracked path; reports/ is gitignored)"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","c085-6d11-d68d-422a"],["parent","86ac-086a-20ad-4327"]],"parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","parent_status_uuid":"fa68be15-a4e4-4984-ae75-76cb25ccbf56","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics"],"ticket_id":"3275-b164-2e9b-4e66","ticket_type":"task","title":"Going-forward metrics snapshot writer/reader (NDJSON)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["ce867deb-d110-4120-8bd8-6a076c0883c9","447960ae-5b45-4b8c-bcde-48de02d2001d","b8865250-f43d-40e4-ab96-c0c67bd992d0","70334b71-c91d-45a0-a330-0531e78ce5ac","843ae5f5-db79-4ea7-8c86-3791ea1f93b0","800de214-cd94-4f85-84f1-028a7ae0931a","f89b505e-443b-4d1b-b601-7fe455883662","fa68be15-a4e4-4984-ae75-76cb25ccbf56","31e1ec76-0b0b-48f3-9a3f-257c09853d80","76b27a3d-271c-4c72-b6b0-22742bbea8b9"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784441650857923284,"uuid":"d4bdcae7-5bbf-43e7-92ca-0001feea7a03"}